title: For Sale:  Rare Antique Long Lee-Enfield BSA Rifle Boer War No.I Mk.I LE 1896 Volley Sight Metford 303 British
postcontent: Rare, original configuration 1896 BSA Long Lee...this first year production Lee-Enfield rifle was manufactured in Birmingham, England and would have been issued into service well prior to the advent of the Second Boer War. The LE I, (Long Lee-Enfield), was an upgrade of the earlier Lee-Metford infantry rifle and featured a 10-round external box magazine, James Paris Lee-designed action, and a 29" barrel with rifling perfected at RSAF Enfield. Britain's standard infantry arm at the end of the Victorian era, this basic model marks a significant moment in small arms history, with the Enfield, in one form or another, going onto to serve with the British military for nearly all of the 20th Century and I accept Money-order,Paypal as my means of payment...Am ready to ship anywhere in the States
